id: 2026-04-14-thread-control-contracts
intent: Add authoritative thread control contracts for hard continuous-run and router-mode supervision.
summary: Introduce sqlite-backed thread control contracts with app-server read/set/release APIs and core/app-server enforcement for continuous and router modes.
change_type: feature
scope: codex-rs app-server protocol, app-server runtime, core session control, sqlite state persistence
decision: Persist thread control contracts in sqlite, expose app-server read/set/release RPCs, cache active control on loaded threads for hard continuous-run gating, and keep router wake scheduling alive across thread lifecycle while limiting router mode to loaded threads.
constraints:
  - Keep the router implementation scoped to loaded threads instead of inventing stored-thread wake/load orchestration.
  - Make thread/control/read reflect active contracts only even though released records remain persisted for auditability.
  - Revalidate router wake-ups against the full active control record before submitting a synthetic wake turn.
